Epizootic ulcerative syndrome, Botswana
-------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 8 Aug 2020 from Dr Letlhogile Modisa, Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Gaborone, Botswana

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 31 Jul 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 31 Jul 2020
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 31 Oct 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Aphanomyces invadans_
Nature of diagnosis: clinical
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Kasane, Chobe
Date of start of the outbreak: 31 Jul 2020
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: river system
Water type: fresh water
Population type: wild
Production system: open
Total animals affected:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Silver catfish (_Schilbe intermedius_) / 2 (scale 0 to 5) / 1 (scale 0 to 5) / 1000 / 32 / 6 / 0 / 0
Banded tilapia (_Tilapia sparrmanii_) / 2 (scale 0 to 5) / 1 (scale 0 to 5) / 253 / 4 / 0 / 0 / 0
Dash tail bard (_Barbus poechi_) / 1 (scale 0 to 5) / 0 (scale 0 to 5) / 1000 / 5 / 0 / 0 / 0
[Squeaker] (_Synodontis_ species) / 4 (scale 0 to 5) / 2 (scale 0 to 5) / 1000 / 32 / 25 / 0 / 0
Red breast Tilapia (_Tilapia rendalli_) / 1 (scale 0 to 5) / 0 (scale 0 to 5) / 1000 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sharptooth catfish (_Clarias gariepinus_) / 1 (scale 0 to 5) / 1 (scale 0 to 5) / 1000 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Blunt-toothed catfish (_Clarias ngamensis_) / 2 (scale 0 to 5) / 0 (scale 0 to 5) / 1000 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: wild fresh water fish in Chobe/Zambezi river system

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Silver catfish (_Schilbe intermedius_) / 0.32 / 0.06 / 18.75 / 0.06
Banded tilapia (_Tilapia sparrmanii_) / 1.58 / 0 / 0 / 0
